trans-unit.source: QPA (Qt Platform Abstraction) platform plugin is used. It provides the basic functionality needed by Qt GUI and Qt Widgets to run against X11. Its library dependencies are described the following table. To build Qt from its source code, you will also need to install the development packages for these libraries for your system.

QPF2 supports anti-aliasing and complex writing systems, using information from the corresponding TrueType font, if present on the system. The format is designed to be mapped directly to memory. The same format is used to share glyphs from non-prerendered fonts between applications.
QPainters that are opened on the image will be scaled. For example, painting on a 200x200 image if with a ratio of 2.0 will result in effective (device-independent) painting bounds of 100x100.
QPainters that are opened on the pixmap will be scaled. For example, painting on a 200x200 image if with a ratio of 2.0 will result in effective (device-independent) painting bounds of 100x100.
QPickEvent::button Returns mouse button that caused the event
QPickEvent::buttons Returns bitfield to be used to check for mouse buttons that may be accompanying the pick event.
QPickEvent::distance Returns distance from camera to pick point
QPickEvent::isAccepted Returns true if the event has been accepted
QPickEvent::localIntersection Returns coordinates of the hit in the local coordinate system of the picked entity
QPickEvent::modifiers Returns bitfield to be used to check for keyboard modifiers that may be accompanying the pick event.
QPickEvent::position Returns mouse pointer coordinate of the pick query
QPickEvent::setAccepted set if the event has been accepted to
QPickEvent::worldIntersection Returns coordinates of the hit in world coordinate system
QPickLineEvent::edgeIndex Returns the index of the picked edge
QPickLineEvent::vertex1Index Returns the index of the first point of the picked edge
QPickLineEvent::vertex2Index Returns the index of the second point of the picked triangle
QPickPointEvent::pointIndex Returns the index of the picked point
QPickTriangleEvent::triangleIndex Returns the index of the picked triangle
QPickTriangleEvent::vertex1Index Returns the index of the first point of the picked triangle
QPickTriangleEvent::vertex2Index Returns the index of the second point of the picked triangle
QPickTriangleEvent::vertex3Index Returns index of third point of picked triangle
